text: Aranucidae is a family of sea slugs, nudibranchs, marine gastropod mollusks in the superfamily Tritonioidea. == Taxonomy == This family is within the clade Cladobranchia (according to the taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi, 2005). The family Aranucidae has no subfamilies (according to the taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi, 2005). ==Genera == * Marianina Pruvot-Fol, 1931 ** Marianina rosea (Pruvot-Fol, 1930) ==References==
title: Aranucidae
